crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a botnet agent, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai families, designed for DDoS attacks and remote command execution. The sample demonstrates several malicious behaviors: 1) C2 Communication: It performs a challenge-response handshake with a hardcoded C2 at 158.94.210.71, utilizing magic values (0x1ceb00da and 0x1ceb32f3) for synchronization. 2) Process Stealth: It uses prctl (PR_SET_NAME) to mask its process name and fork/setsid to daemonize. 3) Competitive Bot Killing: It profiles the system by iterating through /proc to read /cmdline and /maps, likely to identify and terminate competing malware. 4) DDoS Capabilities: The binary contains multiple specialized functions (e.g., sub_401438, sub_400e0b, sub_402286) that craft raw network packets for various flood attacks (TCP, UDP, and application-layer). 5) Obfuscation: It employs internal stream ciphers for data decryption and custom memory management to avoid standard library signatures.
